==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[un-]]'' + ''[[due]]''

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uː|-uː]]

===Adjective===
'''undue'''
#[[Excessive]]; going beyond that what is natural or [[sufficient]].
#:''To individuals who despise killings in any form, death penalty is '''undue''' punishment.'' 
#That which ought not to be done; [[illegal]]; [[unjustified]].
#(''of a payment etc'') Not [[owe|owing]] or [[payable]].

===Derived terms===
*[[undueful]]
*[[undueness]]
*[[unduly]]

